{"blocks":[{"key":"ehm5p","text":"Processing frozen cells for population-scale Oxford Nanopore long-read DNA sequencing SOP","type":"align-left","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":89}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6p7g7","text":"At the NIH's Center for Alzheimer's and Related Dementias (CARD) https://card.nih.gov/research-programs/long-read-sequencing we will generate long-read sequencing data from roughly 4000 patients with Alzheimer's disease, frontotemporal dementia, Lewy body dementia, and healthy subjects. With this research, we will build a public resource consisting of long-read genome sequencing data from a large number of confirmed people with Alzheimer's disease and related dementias and healthy individuals.","type":"align-left","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":65,"length":59}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":65,"length":59}],"data":{}},{"key":"4elim","text":"For this project the long-read sequencing data will be derived from brain tissue, but for benchmarking purposes we also developed a protocol for processing frozen cells.","type":"align-left","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3k22i","text":"The frozen cell protocol was developed to generate long-read sequencing data for the Coriell  human-genome cell-lines that is comparable to the data output of the brain based protocol described herehttps://www.protocols.io/view/processing-human-frontal-cortex-brain-tissue-for-p-kxygxzmmov8j/v2) i.e. targeting an N50 of ~30kb and ~30X coverage.","type":"align-left","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":198,"length":96}],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":198,"length":96}],"data":{}},{"key":"31p62","text":"

